Also, don't push yourself too hard! It's okay to take your own pace!🙏 It's okay 😃 In fact, all necessary updates (for upstream breaking changes) are completed - other trivial updates, such as LSP semantic token support, can be committed to main later in the form of patches, as those updates won't bring any significant changes on the user side. TBH, 0.9 is ready to be merged into main 😄 (well, we still need to implement https://github.com/ayamir/nvimdots/issues/568#issuecomment-1519087408, but this won't take long.) To me, merging 0.9 into main ASAP can avoid many meaningless issues, such as #651 and #653.
